### Analysis of the Main Target Image:

- **Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 12 building blocks arranged in a multi-layered configuration. There are two distinct structures, each with its own set of layers and spatial relationships.
  
- **Spatial Relationships:**
  - The left structure has a base layer composed of two yellow rectangular blocks (one horizontal and one vertical) supporting two orange cylindrical blocks.
  - Above the cylinders, there is a green rectangular block.
  - On top of the green block, there is another yellow horizontal rectangular block.
  - At the very top, there is an orange triangular block.
  - The right structure has a base layer consisting of two orange triangular blocks and one orange cylindrical block.
  - Above these, there is a red curved block.

### Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary:

- **Identified Needed Blocks:**
  - Yellow horizontal rectangular block (index 6)
  - Yellow vertical rectangular block (index 7)
  - Orange cylindrical block (index 9)
  - Green rectangular block (index 5)
  - Red curved block (index 1)
  - Orange triangular block (index 13)

### Assembly Order:
